# Supabase Configuration
# Get these from: https://supabase.com → Your Project → Settings → API

# Replace with your actual Supabase project URL
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co

# Replace with your actual Supabase Anon Public Key
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here

# Note: These are placeholder values. 
# The app will error on startup without valid credentials.
# 
# STEPS TO GET REAL CREDENTIALS:
# 1. Go to https://supabase.com
# 2. Create a new project
# 3. Go to Settings → API
# 4. Copy "Project URL" → VITE_SUPABASE_URL
# 5. Copy "Anon Public Key" → VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
# 6. Replace the placeholder values above
# 7. Save this file
# 8. Restart the dev server (Ctrl+C and npm run dev again)
